[[File:BAHCEP Logo.jpg|thumb|BAHCEP 2012 Logo]]

'''BAHCEP (Beijing And Hong Kong Cultural Exchange Program)''' is an annual exchange initiative organized by the China Study Society, [[HKUSU|Hong Kong University Student's Union]] (CSS, HKUSU). In 2012, the three participating universities include [[Peking University]], [[Tsinghua University]] and the [[University of Hong Kong]]. These are generally considered as the best universities of their respective regions. 20 students from Beijing are going to spend a week in Hong Kong together with local students during their autumn break (29 September - 6 October). The goal of this exchange is to give them an opportunity to communicate freely and come to a mutual understanding. Therefore, unguided face-to-face group discussions are the main focus of this event.

