'''Bhim Public High School''' is located in Bhimeshwor Municipality,Suntwapar [[Dolakha District|Dolakha]]. It is one of the oldest high school in Dolakha District. It is established in 2007 B.S.Most of the students were local. Since there were not any High School in surrounding town or village, most of the students used to come this school for study. Some of the popular teachers were late Dr. Kabitaram Shrestha, Badriman Shrestha, Tirtha Narayan Manandhar, Chok Bahadur Dahal, Shyam Krishna Shrestha. The old building of school was built by the effort of local people from Dolakha Bazaar and some money funded by the government.
