{{Infobox school | name = Victoria College School | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | motto = | established = | opened = | type = | type_label = | district = [[Amman]] | grades = [[K–12 (education)|K-12]] | superintendent = | principal = | viceprincipal = | viceprincipal_label = | enrollment = | faculty = | ceeb = | campus type = | campus size = | mascot = | newspaper = | colors = | location = [[Amman]] | country = [[Jordan]] | coordinates = | website = | feeders = }}
'''Victoria College School''' is a school in [[Amman]], [[Jordan]]. It is from kindergarten through high school. The school has branches in Egypt and Saudi Arabia and other countries.
{{coord missing|Jordan}}
[[Category:Schools in Jordan]] [[Category:Education in Amman]] On the 25th of October 2018, 44 students and staff members had been swept away by floods in the Dead Sea region in Amman, Jordan, whilst on a field trip, which resulted in 18 deaths and 34 injuries in what has been called [[the Dead Sea disaster]] <ref> http://www.jordantimes.com/news/local/least-18-killed-mostly-schoolchildren-flashfloods-sweep-dead-sea-area </ref>
There has been immense backlash aimed at the school following the accident; criticizing that the school allowed the field trip during unstable weather and the fact that the official documents stated that the destination for the field trip was not the Dead Sea but Al Azraq region. The documents also reveal that the approved number of students was 30, when in fact 37 students attended the trip. <ref> https://alghad.com/m/articles/2513142-كتاب-رسمي-يثبت-أن-رحلة-المدرسة-إلى-الأزرق-وليس-للبحر-الميت </ref>
